{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"INTEGRATION RECORD (2026-07-15). This epic was promoted from idea and structured per the operator handoff integrating docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md (143d5074e) into the review-calibration work. Children: E1=e95e (corpora, kappa>=0.7 validity gate), E2=d125 (seeded-defect benchmark, pre-registered thresholds), E3=def5 (counterfactual replay ~200 reviews, ADR-0036 segmented), E5=5342 (cross-gate byte-identical replay), E6=a880 (judge reliability), R7=b1a4 (instrumentation, >=6/8 reproduction gate), R6=5dac (advisory-triage move, ship-first), R2=b080 (operator-attested DET lint, self-gated lexicon eval), R1=59b7 (capability probe, gated E2+E3), R3=3a27 (decomposition-shape, advisory-only, gated E2+E6), R4=03a9 (necessity probe + bug tier, retrospective gate), R5=ea39 (kernel sub-answer, gated E5+E6, IMPACT_MODEL_VERSION bump). OPERATOR DIRECTIVES incorporated: (1) NO A/B testing - validation is eval-based, post-ship validation is dogfooding via R7 metrics, approach documented at each step; (2) NO config-flag/overlay gating - validated changes land directly in the packaged review process (posture stays a registry property; R3 permanently advisory). Sequencing vs the calibration-3 line: R3/R4/R5 depends_on the floor-split story large-sleepful-needlefish (shared criteria_routing.json / review_kernel / sidecar files); experiments E1-E6 have no file overlap and can run alongside. Empirical §5 claims are treated as UNVERIFIED until E1 re-derives them (16/505 edits; 3/8 misses = defect-class identification only, binomial 95% CI 9-76%)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784144149509376001,"uuid":"9b1339fc-e324-4308-a8dc-e8db8c374c6e"}